  "text": "123 HIV/HBV co-infected patients received cART active against HBV (Table 1 ). Median HBsAg levels in patients on therapy were lower by almost 1 log 10 in comparison to untreated individuals (3.32 vs 4.23, P,0.001, Fig 2a) . Comparing HBeAg positive and HBeAg negative patients, the difference in HBsAg levels between untreated and treated HIV/HBV co-infected patients was only significant in HBeAg positive patients (HBeAg positive 4.62 vs 3.71 IU/mL, P = 0.0003; HBeAg-negative 3.53 vs 3.02 IU/mL, P = 0.20). This suggests that anti-HBV therapy has more impact on HBsAg levels in HBeAg positive patients as also seen in HBV mono-infection [CITATION_1] .",
